parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various warning lights and malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the power steering and brakes fail to respond
the vehicle experiences a rough idle
the alternator fails
and the battery drains.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience difficulty starting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the vehicle has difficulty starting
the fuel pump relay fails
and the battery drains.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience electrical system malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The alternator fails
the battery drains
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
and the electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause the vehicle to experience various electrical system malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences various electrical system malfunctions
such as the failure of the fuel pump relay
alternator
and battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repairs can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives notification of a recall
but the part to do the recall repair is unavailable
or the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to extended stopping distances, and in some cases, complete loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the vehicle cannot be stopped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incomplete or faulty recall repairs can lead to the recurrence of brake booster failures, putting drivers and passengers at risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake booster failure recurs after a recall repair
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the vehicle cannot be stopped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or unavailable recall repairs can leave drivers and passengers at risk of accidents or injuries due to brake booster failures.
symptoms: The brake booster failure occurs
but the recall repair is delayed or unavailable
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the vehicle cannot be stopped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of power steering and power brakes, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
often when decelerating or turning
and may not restart immediately. The vehicle may also experience hesitation
misfires
and rough idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel pump relay failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power steering and power brakes, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
often when decelerating or turning
and may not restart immediately. The vehicle may also experience hesitation
misfires
and rough idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The camshaft and lifter failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine may experience misfires
hesitation
and rough idling. The camshaft and lifters may seize
causing engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil pressure sensor failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The engine oil pressure sensor fails
causing the oil temperature to sporadically increase and decrease
leading to engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dashboard issues can cause distraction while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard is wrinkled or has other cosmetic issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel odor and fire can cause accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a fuel odor
and in some cases
a fire may occur.
